*Installation*

1. Extract the contents of "BaseAssualt.rar" somewhere.

2. From the extracted folder, move "BaseAssault.bsp" into your "cstrike\maps" folder.
Default directory path is "C:\Program Files\Steam\SteamApps\YOUR_COUNTERSTRIKE_NAME\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps"

3. If there is no "maps" folder, you can create it and then move "BaseAssault.bsp" into that. (skip this step if there is already a "maps" folder)

4. You have successfully installed the BaseAssault map.



*Other Mods to run alongside this map*

1. This map works best with cssdm (counter-strike source deathmatch). This map is capture and hold, it needs this mod
to complete it. Otherwise taking over the base is pointless because you don't spawn again. It is still playable and enjoyable,
though it becomes campers vs rushers.

2. In order to get cssdm to work, metamod source must also be installed.

3. Source mod is also needed to run the cssdm.

(All these mods can be downloaded here from this webpage:   
http://www.bailopan.net/cssdm/?page=download  )

The sequel to ch_run (look it up)! This game type is a bit different. 

The terrorists are trapped in a standalone, 2-story building, wielding scouts. The CT's, elusive as they are, must maneuver their way to that very building, with only a knife and smoke grenades, find their way to the back ladder, safely climb up, and bust open the box on the top of the building to find their weapon arsenal. From there, it's really anyone's game.

On the CT team, scattering from the spawn is the name of the game, and essential to confuse the scoped terrorists. There are 4 guns strategically placed throughout the map for the CT's, if they choose to fetch them. There are also many explosive barrels placed around the map, to assist the terrorists. Some are hidden behind breakaway walls, some are in the open, yet all are hard for the CT's to see.

There is an AFK killer for the CT's. It's quite fun to watch. They go boom.

After 2 minutes and 30 seconds, a wooden plank atop the T spawn breaks away, releasing the terrorists into the map, to kill off any straggling CT's.

I used a few props and such found in the ch_run map, to express where I got my inspiration, so for the people who played that map before, some things should be mildly reminiscent.

This is my first map I've ever built, and though it might not be the prettiest thing you ever did see, the gameplay itself is what I focused on, and hopefully your server can enjoy it the way ours has. Many hours of fun. Enjoy.

***************Armory & Sniper Battle**********************

VERSION 1.1: I fixed the big glitch where I had a few holes in the ground

- This map I made features two bunkers, one with T and one with CT.

- Each bunker is stocked full of scouts to snipe over to the other side with.

- However, there is a door in each spawn with a keypad, which only YOU as the downloader will get the key code to :)  (It is possible for others to figure out the code but they will probably get sniped in the process)

- Once through the door, there is a room with all of the weapons in the game in it.

- After that, you can choose to go left into the teleporter and spawn out in the middle of the battlefield and run over and throw grenades into the enemy spawn.

....OR...

- Turn right and run down the hallway and go through the door into the enemy spawn and blast them to bits!


So basically, the enemy will be caught COMPLETELY off guard by your assault and all they will have are their scouts :).

Have fun with it!
